010-2014\n|-\n|[[White Sabers Drum and Bugle Corps|White Sabers]]\n|[[Dansville, Livingston County, New York|Dansville, New York]]\n|Classic/Modern\n|1928&ndash;1980, 1994&ndash;present\n|{{Official website | http://whitesabers.org/}}\n|-\n|[[Windsor Regiment Drum and Bugle Corps|Windsor Regiment]]\n|[[West Windsor, New Jersey]]\n|Modern\n|2006&ndash;present\n|{{Official website | http://windsor-regiment.org/}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Notes===\n\n{{Empty section|date=January 2015}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n[[Category:Drum and bugle corps|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of musicians|Drum corps]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues |\n{{Globalize|article|North America|date=January 2013}}\n{{Cleanup|date=January 2015|reason=redlinks and formatting of notes}}\n}}\nThe following is a partial list of '''[[Drum and bugle corps (modern)|drum corps]]''' from the past and present.\n{{details|topic=active drum corps in [[Drum Corps International]]|List of DCI drum corps }}\n\n== Junior corps ==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Corps\n!Location\n!Era\n!Years active\n!Website\n|-\n|[[1st Canadian Regiment (Drum Corps)|1st Canadian Regiment]]\n|[[Edmonton]], [[Alberta]]\n|Modern\n|1977&ndash;1987\n|\n|-\n|[[2nd Decade]]\n|[[Montmagny, Quebec]]\n|Modern\n|1981\n|\n|-\n|[[2nd Signals]]\n|[[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n|\n|?\n|\n|-\n|[[3rd Regiment (Quebec)]]\n|[[Saint-Eustache, Quebec]]\n|Modern\n|1985&ndash;1998\n|\n|-\n|[[3rd Regiment (OR)]]\n|[[Portland, Oregon]]\n|Modern\n|1975&ndash;1977\n|\n|-\n|[[4th Brigade (Drum Corps)|4th Brigade]]\n|[[Saint-J\u00e9r\u00f4me, Quebec]]\n|Classic/Modern\n|1971&ndash;1975\n|\n|- \n|[[5th Col. RCASC]]\n|[[Ontario]]\n|\n|?\n|\n|-\n|[[5th Maine Regiment (Drum Corps)|5th Maine Regiment]]\n|[[Portland, Maine]]\n|Modern\n|1972\n|\n|-\n|[[7th Regiment Drum and Bugle Corps|7th Regiment]]\n|[[New London, Connecticut]]\n|Modern\n|2003&ndash;present\n|{{Official website | http://www.7thregiment.org}}\n|- \n|[[12th Command]]\n|[[Taylor, Michigan]]\n|[[